  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Envisioning the Drawer**\n\nI\'m incredibly pleased with how things are progressing! I\'ve started picturing the `/src/components/IssueDetailDrawer.tsx` file and am excited to build the right-side split drawer. This clean, slide-over drawer will be the perfect way to display issue details.\n\n\n**Designing the Drawer Features**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the drawer\'s content. I\'ve designed the breadcrumb, issue type selector, delete/archive button, and close button, thinking they are important for functionality and project management. The left column will feature an editable summary and AI-powered actions to optimize descriptions, estimate story points, and break down tasks, which is exciting! I\'m particularly excited about the magic of the AI optimization tools, which are super helpful!\n\n\n**Defining Sub-task Functionality**\n\nI\'m working on the drawer\'s content, specifically the sub-tasks! I\'ve designed the ability to instantly populate sub-tasks, including rich markdown description with preview and edit modes, plus a checklist. I\'m excited about the sub-task progress bar! I\'m also planning the comment thread for each issue. Users can add comments, plus delete comments. I\'m focusing on user interface design!\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/src/components/IssueDetailDrawer.tsx` to serve as a right slide-over panel for issue details. It features:\n1. Breadcrumbs, issue type selectors, and delete options.\n2. Full Markdown description rendering with toggleable live edits.\n3. Interactive AI Power Tools (Optimize Description, Predict Story Points with PM rationale, and Break Down into atomic Sub-tasks checklist) utilizing our full-stack Express + Gemini proxy APIs.\n4. Sub-task checklists with inline creation and completion progress metrics.\n5. Work logs with historical tracking.\n6. A comments section allowing user dialogue and real-time updates.\n7. Quick-edit dropdowns for priority, assignee, status, and story points."
    thinking_duration {
