  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Marveling at the Code**\n\nI\'m incredibly impressed by `IssueDetailDrawer.tsx`. The code\'s robustness is striking, packed with features like comprehensive worklogging, AI integrations, state synchronization, and detailed subtasks. It\'s truly a marvel of engineering, and a testament to clever design.\n\n\n**Designing the Copilot Component**\n\nI\'m now focused on `/src/components/AICopilot.tsx`. I\'m envisioning it as a full-fledged AI Sprint Planner Dashboard, acting as an AI scrum coach and product analyst. The component will feature a form for users to describe their goals or desired features, like \"Build an interactive analytics dashboard with D3 line charts and interactive filtering.\" Upon clicking \"Generate Sprint Plan,\" which will include beautiful loading messages, the AI will generate a visual list of proposed Jira Issues (Story, Task, Bug, Epic) that include key, summary, and more data. A button, \"Import to Jira Backlog,\" will instantly add these to the user\'s project.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will now create `/src/components/AICopilot.tsx` to handle the Agile AI Copilot Workspace. It contains:\n1. **Interactive Sprint Goal Planner**: Allows users to enter a product goal (e.g., \"Build a full Stripe subscription checkout checkout flow\") and calls the `/api/ai/generate-sprint` server endpoint to automatically construct a customized backlog of stories, tasks, and bugs.\n2. **Review & Bulk Import**: Allows the user to inspect the generated backlog items, adjust parameters, and import them all at once into the live Jira project.\n3. **Agile Health Check Coach**: Analyzes the active project statistics (unassigned tasks, high-concurrency developer bottlenecks, high-priority bugs, sprint story point distribution) and writes a custom PM audit recommendation."
    thinking_duration {
