  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Orchestrating the App**\n\nI\'m focusing now on orchestrating modules in `/src/App.tsx`. My current focus is to manage the `projects` list, specifically, the Qtum and Apollo integration. I\'ll need to figure out how to maintain the state for this list and keep everything in sync.\n\n\n**Defining App State**\n\nI\'ve defined `activeProjectId` (defaults to QTUM), `sprints`, `issues`, `activeTab`, and `selectedIssue`. I\'m working on how to sync with `localStorage` on component mount, checking for cached Jira workspace state, and seeding with initial data if needed. I also need to save issue/sprint changes. I\'ve also come up with some shared methods!\n\n\n**Refining Core Methods**\n\nI\'ve been working on a suite of methods. I can now generate unique issue keys with `onCreateIssue`, plus future sprints are added by `onCreateSprint`. The `onStartSprint`, `onCompleteSprint`, `onImportIssues`, and `onCreateProject` methods are also implemented, with functionality similar to JIRA. I am quite satisfied with the issue generation.\n\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will write the primary React workspace orchestration in `/src/App.tsx`. It manages the global states of the multi-project agile tracking engine:\n1. **Durable LocalStorage Hooks**: Syncs and retrieves the full state (projects, sprints, issues, and logs) to withstand page refreshes seamlessly, seeding with detailed templates on initial load.\n2. **Project Switching Rail**: Supports switching between the \"Quantum Engine\" backend project and the \"Apollo UI\" client-side project, with support for creating new custom agile projects (e.g., setting a custom project key such as \"STRIPE\").\n3. **Agile State Orchestrator**:\n   - Status changes directly propagate down.\n   - \"Complete Sprint\" moves any unfinished tasks (To Do, In Progress, In Review) back to the Product Backlog, preserving Done states.\n   - \"Start Sprint\" activates a sprint.\n   - Custom issue key generation tracks unique project counters sequentially (e.g., APLO-1, APLO-2).\n4. **Left-Navigation Rail**: Combines the Active Board, Backlog Planner, AI Sprint Copilot, and Project Insights in a layout with typography and UI cues."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 4
      nanos: 269247803
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
