  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Confirming Readiness of Build**\n\nI\'m incredibly pleased to report the development server is up and running. Compilation is now clean and the linter shows green. The Jira clone is essentially completed. I\'ve confirmed that the core types are defined in `/src/types.ts`: Project, Sprint, Issue, Comment, SubTask, and WorkLog. The build appears sound.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have completed building the Jira-like full-stack workspace application. It has been compiled successfully and is running on your development server.\n\nHere is a conceptual and design-focused summary of the workspace:\n\n### \360\237\216\250 Visual & Experience Architecture\n* **Corporate Slate Interface**: Implemented a warm, high-contrast light theme using soft slate backgrounds, clean dividing lines, elegant typography, and generous negative space to minimize visual clutter.\n* **Agile Sidebar Navigation**: Organized workspace screens into responsive navigation sections: **Active Sprint Board**, **Backlog Planner**, **AI Agile Copilot**, and **Reports & Insights**, framed by a project selection selector.\n* **Persistent Local-First State Engine**: Engineered local state synchronization that automatically saves all issue movements, sprints, logged hours, and comments directly to your browser\'s persistent storage, persisting work across page reloads.\n\n### \360\237\233\240\357\270\217 Key Functional Workspaces\n1. **Interactive Kanban Board**: Provides columns (**To Do**, **In Progress**, **In Review**, **Done**) with instant status transition toggles, user assignee card badges, priorities, and a click-to-open detailed review flow.\n2. **Backlog & Sprints Planner**: Distinguishes between the **Active Sprint** (and its statistics), **Planned Future Sprints**, and the **Product Backlog**. Supports shifting issues between sprints, initiating future sprints, and completing sprints (which automatically rolls any incomplete issues back to the backlog).\n3. **Slide-Over Detail Drawer**: Features breadcrumbs, quick issue attribute changes (assignee, priority, status, and story points), a Markdown description editor, an interactive sub-tasks checklist, a comment feed, and time-tracking work logs.\n4. **Agile Reports & Insights**: Aggregates and displays project metrics through interactive progress bars, a customized vector SVG issue-profile donut chart, sprint-by-sprint velocity trackers, and a comprehensive work-log audit trail.\n\n### \342\232\241 Integrated Agile AI Copilot\nPowered server-side using the **Gemini model** to keep sensitive keys hidden:\n* **AI Optimize Description**: Drafts rich, professionally formatted Markdown descriptions including user goals and concrete acceptance criteria.\n* **AI Subtask Breakdown**: Deconstructs high-level story summaries into granular, checklists of subtasks in one click.\n* **AI Estimate Points**: Recommends Scrum story points along with a clear agile PM rationale.\n* **Sprint Goals Roadmapper**: Generates a complete 4-to-7 issue roadmap backlog given any product epic or milestone objective.\n* **Agile Scrum Coach Audit**: Scans active board status to flag workload bottlenecks, unassigned work items, and highest-priority defects."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 1
      nanos: 606856949
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
