    thinking: "**Refining Kanban Board Styling**\n\nOkay, I\'m working on perfectly styling the KanbanBoard with \"Natural Tones.\" The header section will have a workspace container with `bg-[#FDFCF8]` instead of the default `bg-slate-50`. Let me see where I should go next with this.\n\n\n**Updating Header & Filter**\n\nI\'ve updated the header styling with a border, background, and shadow for visual appeal. The upper text will be smaller, uppercase, and a lighter color. I\'ve also defined styling for the title and sub-goal text within the header. Next, the \"Create Issue\" button will be rounded and use `bg-natural-primary`. The filter bar\'s search input looks great with a rounded design and subtle focus effects. I\'m moving on to the dropdown labels now.\n\n\n**Defining Filter Dropdown Styling**\n\nI\'ve specified styling for the filter dropdown select boxes, the \"Clear Filters\" button, and the stat count badges. I\'m focusing on clean, natural-toned elements with rounded corners and subtle visual cues. Next, I\'ll move on to refining the column grid with updated background and border styles.\n\n\n**Styling Issue Cards**\n\nOkay, I\'m now styling the Issue Cards. For the placeholder, I\'ve implemented a dashed border, rounded corners, and subtle background. I\'m focusing on the card container\'s background, border, and hover effects, using natural tones and a shadow. The active state line is very important! Urgent items will have a stylish border reflecting their priority, and I\'ve set up different priority indicators. Finally, I\'m color-coding the issue type badges.\n\n\n**Defining Issue Card Elements**\n\nI\'m now detailing styling for issue card elements. Story badges will be emerald, while features and tasks will be primary-toned. I\'ve set text styles for the title and defined the bottom row with the issue key, story points badge, and assignee avatar. The hover select overlay will use a transition, and the hover select is further styled. Finally, I\'m working on the modal styling.\n\n\n"
